{"name": "b�EVERGREENb� 1/44", "description": "A soil without toil is where I plant my feet. 
I thrive without strife, and flourish with ease. 
Evergreen like the tree, I tower those beneath. 
From my crown all the way down, you can tell I eat my greens. 
Full serving. Heavy on the greens. Hold the envy, please. 
I bare it all as I turn my cheek,  
I am kind, not weak. 
With roots unfaltering, all I ask is that you water me.  
I recoil my coils and move smooth like a well oiled machine. 
I am ever abundant, ever evolving, evergreen.
